<body>
    <h1>OpenFin Q&amp;A</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Date</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Status</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Question</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Answer</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Can the MFE be aware of the 'application' it =
was launched under? Eg</p><p>Our accounts MFE could be split up in 3 applic=
ations, but say only for a specific application we want to listen for x int=
ent, and for another application we want to listen for for y,z intent?</p><=
p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">I'm just wondering how we can make=
 sure that a Intent goes to the right application, if 2 application listen =
to the same intent</span></p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g=
 h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&n=
bsp;</span></span></span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>If you launch three instances of the same MFE=
 under three different openfin application names, the intent will only be s=
ent to one of them not all of them. So even if the MFE registers three diff=
erent intent handlers, only one of them will be invoked - the one that was =
just launched.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Regarding the first point, I'm pretty=
 sure I can add a method to the westpac-one javascript api to return the la=
unched application name. I'll look into it.</p><p>Not <em>exactly </em>the =
most recent one. Effectively yes, but the way it works is that when we reso=
lve the intent to an App, we then launch that App, and the App is assigned =
a unique Identity. The Intent+Context is then passed to that specific Ident=
ity.&nbsp;</p><p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m=
 n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span><=
/span></span></p><p>So there's a direct link between the chosen App and the=
 Intent passing.</p><p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j=
 k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</=
span></span></span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Does an Intent refer to an App ?</p><span><sp=
an class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z=
 ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>in the underlying Openfin model yes you can s=
pecify the target App. But I've hidden that until we see a need for it. So =
the intent does not specify an App. The App is resolved by lookup of the Ap=
p Directory. Then the Intent is guaranteed to be sent to the resolved targe=
t App instance.</p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l=
 m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span=
></span></span><p>If the App is a singleton then we won't allow a new insta=
nce, and the Intent would be passed to the existing instance of an App with=
 that name,.</p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m =
n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span></=
span></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Closed</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>From the navigator MFE, can we open an applic=
ation without having the target application having to listen to an Intent?<=
/p><p><code>Make a Payment</code> opens application: <strong>Make A Payment=
</strong> <code>/galaxy/payment/make-payment</code> . But this application =
does not listen to a specific intent (it just loads the payment initation s=
creens)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h=
 i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak">if there i=
s no Context to be passed with the Intent, does the application have to lis=
ten for the intent? No it doesn't.&nbsp;</span></span><p>that's right - if =
your app does not need to participate in interop (incoming or outgoing inte=
nts and context) then it can be completely unaware it is running in Openfin=
.</p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s=
 t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></span=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Open</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span class=3D"fui-Flex ___1jp83nv f22iagw f10ra9hq f5wk2nc"><span class=
=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img =
class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail" draggable=3D"false=
" height=3D"312" src=3D"623302c6fcbf435bb5a9c89b470f5b7f9874a355f2b8ca561fa=
9cf3305088c86" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1825455422/image-202=
4-9-11_9-50-36.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1726012264813&amp;api=
=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"18254=
55419" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"atta=
chment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-2024-9-11_9-50-36.png" =
data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resourc=
e-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"182545542=
2" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"1" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></sp=
an></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>1 MFE, that has 3 Intent Listeners.&nbsp;</p>
<p>This MFE we split up in 3 applications, but with a shared codebase =3D s=
o shared Intent Listeners.</p>
<p>How can we make sure that when we raise the Intent MakePayment, that is =
goes to the Make A Payment App, instead of any of the 2 other apps (since t=
hey are all listening to the same intents)</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>If the intent is viewPayments, then the Inter=
opBroker will only send that Intent to an App that was opened as ViewPaymen=
tsApp (and its corresponding URL).</p><span><span class=3D"ui-provider a b =
c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak"=
><span>&nbsp;</span></span></span><p>It's not broadcast, its point-to-point=
 delivery of the Intent to the Target App.&nbsp;</p><span><span class=3D"ui=
-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af a=
g ah ai aj ak"><span>&nbsp;</span></span></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-09-10" class=3D"date-past">10 Sep 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
